			</div>
		</section>

		<Section title='About'>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				I was born and brought up in a small village near Thrissur called Kolazhy in Kerala, India.
			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				My early passion for technology led me to pursue a unique course of study after the 7th
				grade. I joined Junior Technical High School, where I learned the basics of carpentry,
				mechanics, and electronics. After completing my 10th grade, my interest shifted towards
				embedded systems and programming, leading me to enroll in a Polytechnic program where I
				obtained my Computer Science Diploma. Following that, I pursued a B.Tech in Computer Science
				and Engineering, which I completed in 2007.
			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				From my childhood days, I developed a keen interest to be a generalist and build businesses
				that make a difference and embarked on multiple side hustles. After graduating, I stumbled
				upon my first job offer at an Ed Tech startup called HeyMath! in Chennai as Software
				Engineer. It was there that I realised the gap between being college smart and possessing
				the actual skills required as a software developer in the business world to make production
				ready code. After gaining sufficient knowledge in the early years of my career, I started
				volunteering as the Campus Connect Chair for a couple of non-profits, educating students
				across colleges in South India. Along with my team, we organised various campus programs,
				events, workshops, and hackathons to bridge the skill gaps between the curriculum and
				real-world tech stacks. Additionally, I was part of managing team for two technology user
				groups in Chennai: the Adobe Flex User Group and the HTML User Group, where we organised
				events, sessions, hackathons, and provided training to the developer community on the latest
				technology trends.
			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				In 2012, I joined Report Bee, an Education Data Analytics company, as a founding team
				member. As the Product Chief of Technology, I worked closely with the founders and CTO to
				build the tech team and develop the product from the ground up. In 2018, XSEED Education
				acquired Report Bee. Time with Report Bee allowed me to understand education landscape
				across the world and collaborate with various experts from governments and publishers such
				as Pearson and Oxford.
			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				In 2019, I decided to take a break from formal work to bond with my family. During next 3
				years we visited 7 countries, relocated to US for my wifeâ€™s research and became dad of two
				amazing boys. Along with all these, I found Collabwrite a consulting agency, through which I
				explored my passion to build and solve growth problems. Collabwrite provided me with
				opportunities to work with several founders and leaders and their challenges in building
				MVPs, product launches, product growth. This allowed me to expand my expertise beyond
				programming, technology, and ed tech.
			</p>
		</Section>
